    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know i should talk to someone but it doesnt change the math of it though. like, if you look at it objectively, everything is just temporary. we work, we consume, we decay. if the end result is always zero, then why is there this massive pressure to keep the struggle going? it feels like i'm just fighting a losing battle against entropy for no reason.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
